00:11:59.140 --> 00:12:01.730
different GitHub repo, different brand.

00:12:01.730 --> 00:12:04.420
And everybody moved to LibreOffice, and basically,

00:12:04.420 --> 00:12:07.410
nobody uses OpenOffice anymore.

00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:11.380
Same thing with some blockchain systems.

00:12:11.380 --> 00:12:14.660
So, Steam was one where there was this thing where the

00:12:14.990 --> 00:12:18.100
developers of a protocol, for some reason that I don't

00:12:18.100 --> 00:12:21.580
quite understand, had particular rights to do things to the protocol

00:12:21.590 --> 00:12:21.780
.

