So, if you look at what any organization does before it

00:15:52.100 --> 00:15:55.790
screws the users over, the number one thing, day zero

00:15:55.830 --> 00:15:59.280
of initialification, is to dismantle the accountability mechanisms,

00:15:59.280 --> 00:15:59.540
right?

00:15:59.540 --> 00:16:03.140
Dismantle anything that will give your users the ability

00:16:03.140 --> 00:16:03.830
to exit.

00:16:03.860 --> 00:16:07.060
So, for example, if you're Instagram or Reddit or

00:16:07.060 --> 00:16:11.480
Twitter, then you're going to turn off your API.

00:16:11.620 --> 00:16:15.780
This happens before the actual, like, the algorithms go to

00:16:15.780 --> 00:16:18.750
shit and your application experience becomes useless.

00:16:18.750 --> 00:16:20.970
First, you turn off the APIs and then you wait a

00:16:20.970 --> 00:16:21.380
bit.

00:16:21.380 --> 00:16:24.190
And that way, nobody else has got a way to help

00:16:24.190 --> 00:16:26.980
you exit, to give you an alternative.

00:16:26.980 --> 00:16:28.380
Another example.

00:16:28.480 --> 00:16:32.780
Week one of the Trump administration, on the first Friday night

