This is a slightly too strong a case, but there's

00:20:58.010 --> 00:21:02.100
this – remember we had recoverable in the four features.

00:21:02.290 --> 00:21:05.400
So there's this feature in DIP PLC where if

00:21:05.400 --> 00:21:08.040
you have a high-profile, like a high-

00:21:08.040 --> 00:21:10.890
priority rotation key and a low-priority

00:21:11.070 --> 00:21:14.700
rotation key, you can cancel the actions of the low priority

00:21:14.700 --> 00:21:16.780
one with the high priority one.

00:21:16.780 --> 00:21:20.200
And this is sort of useful, but it automatically creates this

00:21:20.200 --> 00:21:21.210
fork in your dead, right?

00:21:21.280 --> 00:21:24.040
It automatically causes Sadako to come crawling out of your TV

00:21:24.490 --> 00:21:28.550
screen and reduces your – the security properties of your account.

00:21:28.580 --> 00:21:31.850
So, one more thing.

00:21:31.860 --> 00:21:34.310
If you are hosting PDSs for somebody else, a

00:21:34.310 --> 00:21:37.920
dead rotation key is toxic waste, right?

00:21:37.920 --> 00:21:40.370
Plan the life cycle of your rotation keys.

00:21:40.520 --> 00:21:43.080
If you use – I don't know if this is still

00:21:43.080 --> 00:21:45.140
true, but when I tried it – if you use the

00:21:45.140 --> 00:21:48.900
stock PDS that Blue Sky provided, it will set one

00:21:48.900 --> 00:21:50.500
rotation key for all your users.

00:21:50.500 --> 00:21:55.110
And that means that if one of your users moves off your

00:21:55.180 --> 00:21:58.940
PDS, then you still can't delete it because you

00:21:58.940 --> 00:22:00.040
need it for other users.

00:22:00.040 --> 00:22:01.950
It would be better to do what we do with the signing

00:22:02.010 --> 00:22:05.440
keys and create it when they sign up and then delete it

00:22:05.440 --> 00:22:06.660
if they move off, okay?

00:22:06.660 --> 00:22:11.700
So, all this just makes it – it makes the individual

00:22:12.050 --> 00:22:15.450
user safer, but it also means that in the case where

00:22:15.450 --> 00:22:18.710
we have to do this switch from a rogue PLC directory

00:22:18.710 --> 00:22:21.410
, we have far less ambiguous data that we have to somehow

00:22:21.410 --> 00:22:22.090
